  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <h3>How it works</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>During feed refresh, each new article's content length is checked against the threshold.</li>
      <li>If below the threshold, the extension fetches the linked page and extracts the main content.</li>
      <li>The extracted content replaces the empty feed content and is saved to the database.</li>
      <li>Works with any feed — no per-feed CSS selectors needed.</li>
      <li>The original feed content (if any) is preserved in a collapsible section.</li>
    </ul>
